    "Through this analysis, I aimed to unpack the story hidden behind the churn data, and what I discovered tells us more than just \"who leaves and who stays.\"\n",
    "The first clue came from Monthly Charges. Customers paying higher monthly fees showed a clear tendency to churn more. The relationship wasn't random, it followed a predictable, rising trend. Like an unspoken threshold, once the monthly cost crosses a certain point (around $80), customers begin to question the worth of staying. The logistic model confirmed this intuition, with a statistically significant coefficient indicating that every extra dollar pushes a customer closer to the exit.\n",
